==English==

===Etymology===
Jill is a variant of the proper name [[Gill]], itself a female form either of [[Julius]] (then also Gillian or [[Jillian]]) or of [[Aegidius]].

===Proper noun===
'''Jill'''

#{{given name|female|from Latin|}} A female [[given name]].
# generic use for any female (as [[Sheila]] in Australian English); also in the compound [[jillstrap]] (also shortened as jill), the female counterpart of a [[jockstrap]] 
# A young [[woman]]; a [[sweetheart]].

